{"code":"02160137","about":" \tThe course centers on Project-Based Learning (PBL), one of the methods for learning and assessment. Throughout the course, students will develop relevant instructional competencies and progressively engage in authentic PBL tasks. They will also participate in reflective practices, formative feedback, and assessment processes aimed at evaluating both the process and the final product. Special emphasis will be placed on formative assessment and feedback strategies that enhance student learning.  \tLearning Outcomes:       By the end of the course, students will be able to: 1.\tDesign instructional units in alignment with the principles of Project-Based Learning (PBL). 2.\tLead PBL initiatives in science and technology classrooms. 3.\tProvide formative feedback that enhances learning for both peers and students. 4.\tDevelop rubrics for assessing both the processes and products of learning. 5.\tImplement formative assessment strategies throughout all phases of the PBL. 6.\tEngage in self-reflection and self-assessment practices.","points":2.5,"name":"למידה מבוססת פרויקטים","connections":{"dependencies":[],"adjacent":[],"exclusive":[]},"seasons":["Winter","Spring","Summer"],"faculty":"חינוך למדע וטכנולוגיה","current":true}